## âœ… 3. Do users need to *hold TEA* before they can pay?

Yes â€” **holding TEA first is the norm**. You donâ€™t want payments to fail or swap unpredictably.

### âœ… Common Design Patterns:

| Model                                       | Example                               |
| ------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| **Hold TEA = get discount**                 | â€œGet 10% off if you pay in TEAâ€       |
| **Must pay in TEA**                         | Required to use TEA to complete bill  |
| **Hybrid:** pay in MATIC, get points in TEA | Still rewards TEA as loyalty currency |

You can even **mint points only if payment was in TEA**, to incentivize behavior.

